        "client_msg_id": "879638b0-e973-4f4a-9c28-afc7f6eebee2",
        "text": "This boils down to dynamic vs static mindset. It’s like bikes vs cars. Fast, lightweight vs safe, stable. Some debates never end or are they just programmer road rage ? I’m pretty sure people had the same debates about planes and zeppelins. Numerically it would be &gt; 4x in terms of development time improvement going by bikes vs cars analogy, especially for dynamic languages. I think it would be best to compare loc for  common tasks between the two. Json parsers are faster than xml parsers probably.",
